### [High] ERC1155 Pass Transfer Bypasses Per-Address Attendance Tracking, Enabling Unlimited BEAT Farming

**Affected Files:** src/FestivalPass.sol

**Description**

Users purchase ERC1155 festival passes and earn BEAT tokens by calling `attendPerformance`. Two guards prevent double-claiming: `hasAttended[performanceId][msg.sender]` blocks re-attendance, and `lastCheckIn[msg.sender]` enforces a 1-hour cooldown. Both guards are tracked per caller address, not per pass token. ERC1155 passes are freely transferable. After attending, a user can transfer their pass to a fresh wallet — that wallet has `hasAttended == false` and `lastCheckIn == 0`, bypassing both guards immediately.

```solidity
function attendPerformance(uint256 performanceId) external {
    require(isPerformanceActive(performanceId), "Performance is not active");
    require(hasPass(msg.sender), "Must own a pass");
@>  require(!hasAttended[performanceId][msg.sender], "Already attended this performance");
@>  require(block.timestamp >= lastCheckIn[msg.sender] + COOLDOWN, "Cooldown period not met");
    // Both checks are per-address — a fresh wallet bypasses them immediately

    hasAttended[performanceId][msg.sender] = true;
    lastCheckIn[msg.sender] = block.timestamp;

    uint256 multiplier = getMultiplier(msg.sender);
    BeatToken(beatToken).mint(msg.sender, performances[performanceId].baseReward * multiplier);
}
```

**Risk**

- Executing this attack requires only a `safeTransferFrom` call and a second funded wallet.
- A BACKSTAGE pass (3× multiplier) costs 0.25 ETH. With 10 wallets, an attacker earns 10 × baseReward × 3 BEAT from a single pass purchase.

**Impact**

- BEAT token supply becomes unbounded from a single pass purchase, undermining token scarcity and memorabilia pricing.
- Legitimate attendees cannot accumulate enough BEAT to redeem memorabilia as attackers drain performance rewards.

**Proof of Concept**

```solidity
function test_PassTransferFarming() public {
    address alice = makeAddr("alice");
    address bob   = makeAddr("bob");
    vm.deal(alice, 1 ether);

    vm.prank(alice);
    festivalPass.buyPass{value: 0.25 ether}(3);

    vm.prank(organizer);
    uint256 perfId = festivalPass.createPerformance(
        block.timestamp + 1 hours, 4 hours, 100e18
    );
    vm.warp(block.timestamp + 90 minutes);

    vm.prank(alice);
    festivalPass.attendPerformance(perfId);
    assertEq(beatToken.balanceOf(alice), 15e18 + 300e18);

    // Alice transfers pass to Bob — both guards reset to zero
    vm.prank(alice);
    festivalPass.safeTransferFrom(alice, bob, 3, 1, "");

    // Bob attends the SAME performance — succeeds
    vm.prank(bob);
    festivalPass.attendPerformance(perfId);
    assertEq(beatToken.balanceOf(bob), 300e18);
    // One pass → 600e18 BEAT. Repeat with N wallets for N × 300e18.
}
```

**Recommended Mitigation**

```diff
+ function safeTransferFrom(
+     address from, address to, uint256 id, uint256 amount, bytes memory data
+ ) public override {
+     require(id > BACKSTAGE_PASS, "Festival passes are non-transferable");
+     super.safeTransferFrom(from, to, id, amount, data);
+ }
+
+ function safeBatchTransferFrom(
+     address from, address to, uint256[] memory ids, uint256[] memory amounts, bytes memory data
+ ) public override {
+     for (uint256 i = 0; i < ids.length; i++) {
+         require(ids[i] > BACKSTAGE_PASS, "Festival passes are non-transferable");
+     }
+     super.safeBatchTransferFrom(from, to, ids, amounts, data);
+ }
```

